Daniels Igoni, Yenagoa The Speaker of the Bayelsa State House of Assembly, Monday Bubou-Obolo, on Tuesday inaugurated a member representing Brass Constituency I, Charles Daniel. Daniel of the All Progressives Congress was declared winner of the constituency’s election conducted by the Independent National Electoral Commission on November 16. The state Resident Electoral Commissioner, Monday Udoh, issued him a certificate of return on November 21 alongside the state governor-elect, David Lyon, of the APC in Yenagoa. With Daniel’s swearing in, the APC now has five members in the 24-member Bayelsa State House of Assembly while the ruling Peoples Democratic Party has 19. Meanwhile, the state House of Assembly has passed the Legislative Fund Management Bill, 2019, which confers financial autonomy on the assembly. Bubou-Obolo explained during an emergency sitting of the assembly that the bill would give the state legislature the power to manage its funds henceforth. The assembly also received the reports of its committee on public service establishment on the House of Assembly Service Commission. CopyrightPUNCH.
